<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Further notes for Commons Science and Technology Committee _x000b_Inquiry into Women in STEM careers</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Supplementary written evidence submitted by </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The Open University</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> (WSC0102)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Additional information about the Open University</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Flexible working</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Although scientific research in academia</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> can require long hours, there are opportunities to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">introduce the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">flexibility</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to do the work at different times and from different locations. It is important to let go of assumptions about where work gets done and how it is done.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The OU has a strong track </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">record in flexible working and remote working using technologies because of our distributed structure</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. Academic staff based in our 13 regional and national centres can regularly join meetings and collaborate on both teaching and research via our internal v</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ideo and audio conferencing systems. All meetings at our Milton Keynes campus are held within core hours to allow for travel </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">which has the additional benefit for those who need flexibility for caring commitments.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Our</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><a href="http://www.open.ac.uk/researchprojects/open-science/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Open Science </span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Laboratory</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is at the forefront of developing new research methods and pedagogies for conducting experiments at a distance.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Women Returners to STEM</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Between 2005 and 2011</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the Open University</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> ran a programme </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for women </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">returning to STEM careers after a career break</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">which</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> over 1000 women </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STEM graduates </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">participated</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">As well as 100 hours of online learning,</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the women, who had previously worked in a range of STEM professions both in academia and industry,</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> were able to interact in online forums, and meet each other at local networking events.  A </span><a href="http://oro.open.ac.uk/36328/2/GWO2012-final.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">r</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">ecent evaluation</span></a><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> showed </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">over 70% of women had</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> return</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ed</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to employment in STEM</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> five years after takin</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">g part in the programme. </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> was an externally funded project and w</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e would recommend further funding to support such initiatives in future.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Evidence based solutions</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Open University hosts, edits and publishes the </span><a href="http://genderandset.open.ac.uk"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline">International Journal of Gender Science and Technology</span></a><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. This was originally set up in 2009 and funded via the UK Resource Centre for Women in SET and since the funding ended in 2011 has continued to be support</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ed by </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">he Open University in recognition of the important role this journal plays in bridging the boundaries between policy, practice and research. As an open access free online journal we are able to disseminate robust peer reviewed international research</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to a wide community of stakeholders to help inform developments in this area.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Recommendations</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We are concerned </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that the short term nature of funding for interventions in this area means there is a danger of losing momentum and having to regularly </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">reinvent solutions. This is exemplified by the ending</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">funding for </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">UK Resource Centre for Women</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in SET</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> which between 2004 and 2011 did </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">an </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">enormous amount of work in </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">supporting</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> women </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in STEM across the UK both in education and employment, including ac</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ademia. We would urge that further commitment of resources </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">should</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> be sustainable and long term. </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">There is a need for </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">regular update on statistics to ensure monitoring of progress can be achieved against agreed benchmarks. </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We r</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ecommend funding </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be made a</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">vailable </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to produce </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">an update to the</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><a href="http://www.theukrc.org/files/useruploads/files/final_sept_15th_15.42_ukrc_statistics_guide_2010.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">UKRC</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline"> Statistics Guide </span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">2010</span></a><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">.</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Universities should provide dedicated research time </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for women </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">following maternity leave </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">(or men returning from adoption or parenting leave). S</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ome universities are </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">already doing this and have been </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">able to provide costs for this, but not all. Could research councils offer a bursary fund that universities could apply fo</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">r?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Role models </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">should not only include</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> women but also role models of successful men who work part time and take on caring roles</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">so </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">it </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is not only</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> women who are always seen as </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">being responsible for childcare. Women scientist role models are problemat</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ic as they are often intertwined with personal biographies about their partners and children in a way that men’s stories are not</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, so parity about how role models are portrayed is needed</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">UK Research Councils should follow the example of the </span><a href="http://genderedinnovations.stanford.edu/sex-and-gender-analysis-policies-major-granting-agencies.html"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Irish Research Council</span></a><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and r</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">equire all research bids to include a statement on sex-gender dimensions and implications of the research proposal</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Universities </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">should</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> actively encourage more women to apply for European Research Council (ERC) grants.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The number of grants awarded to women for the first six completed calls is one fifth overall, and drops from 25% for women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tarting </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">G</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">rantees to 12% for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women awarded the Advanced Grants. (ERC 2010: 33) Current research suggests that women are not put forward or encouraged to put themselves forward because the criteria stipulate excellence and future leaders</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">hip</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, and women are less confident about making th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ose sort</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of claims for themselves</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> at an early career stage</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; color:#231f20; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The role of journals and publishers needs to be emphasised. Publication is key to successful career development </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for women in STEM </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">but evidence shows women are less likely to get published, to </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be first authors, to be on editorial boards. Unconscious bias can thus affect women’s careers outside of</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> academic</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> institution</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We r</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ecommend that the committee are aware of the work of </span><a href="http://www.ease.org.uk/about-us/organisation-and-administration/gender-policy-committee"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">EASE Gender Parity Committee</span></a><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> which is trying to get scientific journals to tackle this</span><span style="color:#010101; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="color:#231f20; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>